  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_0' aria-label=\" Jharkhand Urja Utpadan Nigam Ltd. & Anr. versus M/s Bharat Heavy Electricals Limited pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('0','2025','2025_4_1646_1661','2025INSC533'); ><font size='4'> <strong>JHARKHAND URJA UTPADAN NIGAM LTD. & ANR.<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>M/S BHARAT HEAVY ELECTRICALS LIMITED </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 4 S.C.R. 1646</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 533</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010005312025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : J.B. PARDIWALA, R MAHADEVAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration The High Court rejected the Interim Application No. 11269 of 2024 filed by the petitioner herein u/s.5 of the Limitation Act, 1963 and thereby declined to condone the delay of 301 days in filing the main appeal u/s.13(1-A) of the Headnotes&dagger; Commercial Courts Act, 2015 &ndash; ss.13(1-A), 16 &ndash; Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 &ndash; Order XX Rule 1 &ndash; Limitation Act, 1963 &ndash; s.5 &ndash; Respondent instituted a civil suit against the Petitioner for recovery of a sum of money along with interest on<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 15-04-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> SPECIAL LEAVE PETITION (CIVIL) No. 9580/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Dismissed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('0','2025','2025_4_1646_1661','2025INSC533','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=op